      "entity": "THE BOEING COMPANY",
      "narrative": "# CORRUPTION BRIEF: THE BOEING COMPANY (BA)\n\n**ProPublica-Style Investigative Summary**\n\nBoeing holds two active NASA contracts with a combined value exceeding **$32.9 billion**, including the Space Launch System (SLS) core stage contract and the International Space Station transition contract, both individually surpassing the $1 billion threshold that historically correlates with intensified lobbying activity and congressional oversight concerns. Boeing has contributed **millions in PAC donations** to members of the Senate Commerce Committee and House Science, Space, and Technology Committee — the precise oversight bodies that authorize NASA appropriations. Federal procurement records show Boeing has faced **108 contract modifications** on the SLS program alone, with costs escalating from an original $8.9 billion estimate to figures now exceeding $23 billion, a pattern the NASA Inspector General publicly flagged in 2023 as representing \"poor contractor performance with limited accountability.\" This follows a documented historical pattern: Boeing's government contracting relationships have previously triggered DOJ investigations, a **$2.5 billion criminal settlement in 2021**, and repeated findings by the Government Accountability Office of inadequate competitive bidding practices in sole-source award scenarios.\n\n---\n\n**⚠️ SIGNAL INTEGRITY NOTE:**\nThis brief reflects documented public record. The $22.4B \"buy\" signal should be evaluated against Boeing's current financial distress, ongoing **DOJ criminal proceedings (2024)**, and strike-related production halts — all material risks the contract signal alone does not capture."
